From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dev <dev@x>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +1000
Subject: [PATCH] v4.14: runtime /config endpoint with rollback + release tag in caps (#224)

POST /config switches whisper_model and/or compute_type at runtime so
subarr's guided setup can live-apply a model choice without an env edit
and container restart. SAFETY CONTRACT: the endpoint always ends on a
working model -- on any load failure (unknown weights, OOM) it restores
the previous globals and re-loads the prior model, reporting the outcome
(422 reason oom/load_failed). It refuses with 409 while anything is
queued, processing, or running as a direct task (mirrors the
perform_model_cleanup idle check) because a mid-job model swap would
corrupt the run. Inputs are allow-listed (faster-whisper model names and
compute types). Also bakes the GHCR release tag
(SUBARR_SUBGEN_RELEASE_TAG, default 'dev') into the /queue body so
subarr's update check compares tags like-for-like, and advertises
capabilities.runtime_config. Bumps subarr_subgen_patch_rev to v4.14.
Accepted race (matches the perform_model_cleanup precedent): a job
submitted after the idle check but before the swap completes can hit a
model mid-teardown; the lock covers only the read. Low severity at the
endpoint's intended call-site (guided setup on an idle system).

---
